    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Make your balsamic dressing</strong></p>\n<p>Peel and chop the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely. </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>  <strong>sugar</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>to a small bowl.</p>\n<p>Whisk thoroughly with a fork until fully combined.</p>\n<p>Use the next 10 minutes to set the table, wash up or simply chill.</p>",
