    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Finishing preparing your polenta chips</strong></p>\n<p>Once set, turn the <strong>polenta</strong> out onto a chopping board and, using a sharp knife, slice it very carefully into 1.5-2cm thick chips.</p>\n<p>Gently add the<strong> polenta chips</strong> to an oiled baking tray, drizzle with<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>.</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 35 minutes or until the <strong>polenta</strong> <strong>chips</strong> are brown and crispy.</p>\n<p> </p>",
